\shape italic
.

\shape default
 For 
\begin_inset Formula $a_{2}\in\overline{\mathbb{R}}_{>0}$
\end_inset

, a function 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha:\left[0,a_{2}\right)\to\mathbb{R}_{\geq0}$
\end_inset

 belongs to class 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{K}$
\end_inset

 (denoted 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha\in\mathcal{K}$
\end_inset

) if it is (i) strictly increasing, (ii) continuous, and (iii) satisfies
 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha\left(0\right)=0$
\end_inset

.
 A function 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha\in\mathcal{K}$
\end_inset

 is also of class 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{K}_{\infty}$
\end_inset

 (denoted 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha\in\mathcal{K}_{\infty}$
\end_inset

) if 
\begin_inset Formula $a_{2}=\infty$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\lim_{s\to\infty}\alpha\left(s\right)=\infty$
\end_inset

.
 A function 
\begin_inset Formula $\ell:\mathbb{R}_{\geq0}\to\mathbb{R}_{\geq0}$
\end_inset

 belongs to class 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathfrak{L}$
\end_inset

 (denoted 
\begin_inset Formula $\ell\in\mathfrak{L}$
\end_inset

) if it is (i) continuous, (ii) strictly decreasing, and (iii) 
\begin_inset Formula $\lim_{s\to\infty}\ell\left(s\right)=0$
\end_inset

.
 A function 
\begin_inset Formula $\beta:\mathbb{R}_{\geq0}\times\mathbb{R}_{\geq0}\to\mathbb{R}_{\geq0}$
\end_inset

 is said to be of class 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{KL}$
\end_inset

 (denoted 
\begin_inset Formula $\beta\in\mathcal{KL}$
\end_inset

) if it is (i) continuous, (ii) for each fixed 
\begin_inset Formula $s\in\mathbb{R}_{\geq0}$
\end_inset

, the map 
\begin_inset Formula ${\tt r}\mapsto\beta\left({\tt r},s\right)$
\end_inset

 belongs to class 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{K}$
\end_inset

, and (iii) for each fixed 
\begin_inset Formula ${\tt r}\in\mathbb{R}_{\geq0}$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $s\mapsto\beta\left({\tt r},s\right)$
\end_inset

 belongs to class 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathfrak{L}$
\end_inset

.
 A function 
\begin_inset Formula $\beta\in\mathcal{KL}$
\end_inset

 also belongs to class 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{KL}_{\infty}$
\end_inset

 (denoted 
\begin_inset Formula $\beta\in\mathcal{KL}_{\infty}$
\end_inset

) if for each fixed 
\begin_inset Formula $s\in\mathbb{R}_{\geq0}$
\end_inset

, the map 
\begin_inset Formula ${\tt r}\mapsto\beta\left({\tt r},s\right)$
\end_inset

 is class 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{K}_{\infty}$
\end_inset

 
