Using Leibniz's rule, the time derivative of a convolutional integral satisfies
 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{{\rm d}}{{\rm dt}}(e^{-\lambda_{P}t}\ast\mathscr{C})=\mathscr{C}(t)-\lambda_{P}\int_{t_{0}}^{t}e^{-\lambda_{P}(t-\tau)}\mathscr{C}(\tau){\rm d}\tau$
